result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jonathon Mathias Vogel in court with attorney James C. McLaughlin.  Defendant Jonathon Mathias Vogel in custody.  Thomas H Frost appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case and appearances.  Also has 14 CF 73.    Court questions Mr. Vogel regarding his plea questionaire and waiver of rights.  Court finds there is a factual basis and that the def. freely and knowingly waives his rights.  Court speaks to the def. 
  


Count 1-14 CF 65---Defendant pleas no contest. Court accepts plea and finds the def. guilty. 



Count 1-14 CF 73----Dismissed and Read-In



Court orders a PSI-agent need not appear. 
Def. will be at Dodge Correctional on the 16th of February.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for March 30, 2015 at 03:30 pm.
Plea hearing on February 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney James C. McLaughlin in court.  Thomas H Frost appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Also has 14 CF 73 INIT.  Atty McL waived reading in 14 CF 65 and 14 CF 73.  Court addressed the defendant as to his right to a preliminary exam.  Defendant does not wish to have a prelim.  Court finds defendant has freely waived his right to a prelim and binds the defendant over for trial in both files.  Plea hearing scheduled for February 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Preliminary hearing on January 26, 2015 at 02:00 pm.

Attorney James C. McLaughlin in court.  Thomas H Frost appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Also has other file(s).  Officer Lang is here.  State requests warrant.  Atty McL addressed the Court.  Court warrant ordered.
